Class SecurityContextProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vapi.dsig.json.SecurityContextProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JsonOAuthProcessor, JsonSessionProcessor, JsonUserPassProcessor
    public abstract class SecurityContextProcessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements RequestProcessor
    This is an abstract processor that inserts the appropriate security context data into the request. Is is an extension point for third party authentication schemes.

        Processes and possibly modifies the provided request byte array
        Specified by:
        process in interface RequestProcessor
        Parameters:
        request - must not be null. If text is passed as it MUST be UTF-8 encoded.
        metadata - provides additional metadata to the processor that will be passed to the rest of the processor chain. Must not be null. The content under the RequestProcessor.SECURITY_PROC_METADATA_KEY key will be put in the request's ExecutionContext.SecurityContext under the same key i.e. will be accessible by the authentication handlers.
        vapiRequest - the vapi request structure. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        the result of the processor. Must not be null. If text is returned it MUST be UTF-8 encoded.
